description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for an enthusiastic and motivated Band 4 paediatric play specialist, to join the Paediatric team based within the child Health unit at Frimley Park Hospital within Frimley Health. The Trust comprises of three hospital sites covering the communities in Surrey, Hampshire and Berkshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work within an integrated children’s service providing care to children and their families in the Acute, Neonatal, Ambulatory, Learning Disability sectors. The Acute Inpatient Unit offers a wide range of experience, caring for children and young people with medical, surgical, orthopedic and oncology conditions. In addition to the inpatient department, paediatric care is supported within a children’s assessment unit, outpatient unit and day case surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint a well-organised, motivated and enthusiastic person to join our team. The post of play specialist requires a dynamic forward thinking person, to join the existing play team. The role will involve delivering distraction, theatre preparation and general play to all children of all ages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a team of nurses from the Trust in taking forward the nursing vision and Trust values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must have Level Four Diploma in specialized play for sick children and Young people/EDEXCEL Cert in hospital play specialism/HPSC/HPSEB&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Or Foundation degree in health care play specialism&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Wilson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tel: 01276 604252&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email: Katie.wilson25@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
